I'm using a Galaxy nexus, and I'm just trying to get the game to save it's state and data in the game world if they should hit the back button or the home button.

I put this in my code: 

<code>
protected override void OnExiting(object sender, EventArgs args)
        {
           UnloadContent();
            base.OnExiting(sender, args);
        }</code>

I tossed in a break point to see if it works, and neither hitting back button or home button calls the function, it just exits out of the game. What am I doing wrong?
